.TH SIMPLE_SHELL 1 "January 2025" "Version 1.0" "User Commands"

.SH NAME
simple_shell \- A minimal command-line shell

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B simple_shell
.RI [ \-h ]

.SH DESCRIPTION
.B simple_shell
is a lightweight, minimalistic command-line interpreter that provides basic functionality for executing commands and managing processes.

.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-h
Displays help information about the shell.

.SH FEATURES
- Executes commands by searching for them in the PATH environment variable.
- Supports input/output redirection (`<`, `>`).
- Handles background processes using `&`.
- Supports built-in commands:
.TP
.B cd [DIR]
Change the current working directory to DIR.
.TP
.B exit [STATUS]
Exit the shell with an optional exit STATUS.
.TP
.B help
Display a list of built-in commands.

.SH USAGE
Start the shell by typing:
.RS
.B simple_shell
.RE

Enter commands as you would in a standard shell. Use redirection and pipelines for more complex operations.

.SS Examples
.TP
Running a command:
.EX
ls -la
.EE
.TP
Exiting the shell:
.EX
exit 0
.EE
.TP
Running a process in the background:
.EX
sleep 10 &
.EE
.TP
Redirecting output to a file:
.EX
echo "Hello, world" > output.txt
.EE

.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B PATH
Used to locate executable files.
.TP
.B HOME
Used by the `cd` command when no argument is provided.

.SH EXIT STATUS
The exit status is 0 for success and non-zero for failure. If a command fails,
.B simple_shell
returns the exit status of the last executed command.

.SH FILES
.TP
.B README.md
Contains detailed documentation for the project.
.TP
.B man_1_simple_shell
The manual page for the shell.
.TP
.B AUTHORS
Lists contributors to the repository. The authors are:
.RS
